  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a developer, I want to leverage thread pools so that I don't incur the cost of creating a new thread every time.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: There is some old code that is too simplistic and just creates a new `Thread` object every time, instead of pushing a new action into a `ThreadPool`.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nWhen there is code that needs to run in a background thread, we'd post that to a thread pool instead of creating a new short-lived thread specifically for that.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nA new `Thread` object is created everytime (see e.g. [JSCJail.java](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/develop/modules/react-native-status/android/src/main/java/im/status/ethereum/module/JSCJail.java#L105))\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n[comment]: # (Please summarise the solution and provide a task list on what needs to be fixed.)\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\n- [ ] Save a global reference to a [shared thread pool](https://developer.android.com/reference/java/util/concurrent/Executors.html#newCachedThreadPool())\r\n- [ ] Replace situations where we're creating a new thread by usage of the saved thread pool\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n[comment]: # (Android or iOS.)\r\n* Operating System: Android",
